---
<BaseLayout title="Tokenwright — a factory for personal DAOs">

  <!-- ============================================================
       00. MASTHEAD
       ============================================================ -->
  <header class="masthead">
    <div class="topbar">
      <span class="brand mono">tokenwright.ai</span>
      <nav>
        <a href="#02-roster">roster</a>
        <span class="sep">·</span>
        <a href="https://connoratkins.ai/blog/the-token-economy" rel="noopener">thesis</a>
        <span class="sep">·</span>
        <a href="#06-founders">founders</a>
        <span class="sep">·</span>
        <a href="#07-contact">contact</a>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <div class="title-block">
      <div>
        <h1 class="project-title">Tokenwright</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          <span class="accent-label">// spec:</span> a factory for personal DAOs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="revision-stamp">
        <span class="label">REVISION</span>
        <span class="value">DRAFT.00.01 · 2026-04-17</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ============================================================
       01. THESIS
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="01-thesis">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div class="section-number">01 — THESIS</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">The unit of the new economy is the agent-staffed organisation</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="content-row">
      <div class="content-body">
        <p>
          Software-as-a-service is collapsing into personalisation-as-a-service, and
          personalisation-as-a-service is already being overtaken by a larger unit:
          the agent-staffed organisation. A language model is a tokens-in, tokens-out
          function. A harness around one model is a personal agent. A harness over a
          coordinated set of harnesses, each occupying a role that historically
          belonged to a named human operator, is a company. Not a chatbot. Not a
          workflow. A company — the same kind of thing that ships products and holds
          a position in the world — rendered as files instead of headcount.
        </p>
        <p>
          Tokenwright builds those organisations. It is a meta-company: its output is
          other companies. Every executive seat in a traditional firm is a pattern,
          built by the few people who occupied it best. The Bezos seat reads its
          inbox the way the 1997 shareholder letter says to read it. The Jobs seat
          asks <em>what should we not do?</em> before it asks anything else. The
          Karpathy seat keeps a teaching log because that is how it learns. The
          personas are documented in primary material. The harness reproduces the
          operating discipline, not the surface affect.
        </p>
        <p>
          The first test run is Tokenwright itself. The seats operate the
          meta-company, and the meta-company improves the harness that improves
          the seats. If the pattern cannot ship its own institution, it has no
          business being offered to anyone else's. If it can, there is a company
          to show for it — not a demo.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="content-margin">
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// ref:</span> the published thesis — <a href="https://connoratkins.ai/blog/the-token-economy" rel="noopener">The Token Economy</a> (2026-04-17). Argues the token-engineering frame; this site argues the organisation-engineering one.
        </div>
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// prior art:</span> OpenClaw — <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw" rel="noopener">openclaw/openclaw</a>. The file-based personal-agent harness that proved the pattern at the level of a single operator.
        </div>
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// precedent:</span> the OS became the unit once hardware commoditised. The DAO becomes the unit once the agent commoditises.
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       02. THE ROSTER
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="02-roster">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div class="section-number">02 — THE ROSTER</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Ten seats, ten operators, one configuration</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="content-row">
      <div class="content-full">
        <p style="max-width: 68ch;">
          The cast is the anchor. Each seat inherits an operating discipline drawn
          from primary material: shareholder letters, engineering interviews, product
          keynotes, research papers, investment decks, advertising textbooks. The
          seats are not impressions. They are templates.
        </p>

        <div class="roster">
          {roster.map((seat) => (
            <article class="seat">
              <div class="seat-id mono">{seat.id}</div>
              <div class="seat-name">{seat.name}</div>
              <div class="seat-role">{seat.role}</div>
              <div class="seat-question">&ldquo;{seat.question}&rdquo;</div>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="caption">
          <span class="caption-key">Fig. 01</span> — company roster, configuration A (2026-04-17)
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       03. HOW A DAO IS SPECIFIED
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="03-specification">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div class="section-number">03 — SPECIFICATION</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">How a DAO is specified</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="content-row">
      <div class="content-body">
        <p>
          Every seat is a harness: a model plus a set of files that give it identity,
          stance, context, tools, and memory. The company is a harness over those
          harnesses — the same artefact, applied one layer up. A new collaborator can
          read the company by reading the files. A change in how the company behaves
          is a pull request, not a parameter sweep.
        </p>
        <p>
          The principal — the founder — sits at the centre. Context flows inward from
          sources the principal trusts. Work products flow outward from seats the
          principal convenes. Coordination between seats is explicit, written,
          auditable. Nothing in the system is opaque except the weights themselves,
          and the weights are replaceable.
        </p>

        <div class="schematic-wrap">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 640 340" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Schematic of a DAO: user at centre, seats on a ring, context flowing in, work products flowing out.">
            <!-- outer ring of seats -->
            <circle class="line" cx="320" cy="170" r="130" stroke-dasharray="2 4"/>

            <!-- centre node: USER / PRINCIPAL -->
            <rect class="center-node" x="280" y="150" width="80" height="40"/>
            <text class="node-label" x="320" y="174" text-anchor="middle">PRINCIPAL</text>

            <!-- seat nodes around the ring (8 illustrative pins) -->
            <g>
              <circle class="node" cx="320" cy="40" r="10"/>
              <text x="320" y="26" text-anchor="middle">CEO-AXIS</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="412" cy="78" r="10"/>
              <text x="420" y="68" text-anchor="start">CPO</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="450" cy="170" r="10"/>
              <text x="466" y="174" text-anchor="start">CAIO</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="412" cy="262" r="10"/>
              <text x="420" y="278" text-anchor="start">CIO</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="320" cy="300" r="10"/>
              <text x="320" y="320" text-anchor="middle">CRMO</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="228" cy="262" r="10"/>
              <text x="220" y="278" text-anchor="end">COO</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="190" cy="170" r="10"/>
              <text x="174" y="174" text-anchor="end">CEO</text>

              <circle class="node" cx="228" cy="78" r="10"/>
              <text x="220" y="68" text-anchor="end">CENG</text>
            </g>

            <!-- arrows: context in (left), work products out (right) -->
            <g>
              <line class="line" x1="40" y1="170" x2="176" y2="170" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
              <text x="40" y="158" text-anchor="start">CONTEXT IN</text>

              <line class="line" x1="464" y1="170" x2="600" y2="170" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
              <text x="600" y="158" text-anchor="end">WORK PRODUCTS OUT</text>
            </g>

            <defs>
              <marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="8" refX="9" refY="4" orient="auto">
                <path d="M0,0 L10,4 L0,8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/>
              </marker>
            </defs>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="caption">
          <span class="caption-key">Fig. 02</span> — DAO schematic, user-centred
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="content-margin">
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// pattern:</span> harness-of-harnesses. Each seat has its own <span class="mono">IDENTITY</span>, <span class="mono">SOUL</span>, <span class="mono">MEMORY</span>; the company has its own <span class="mono">COMPANY</span> and <span class="mono">ROSTER</span>.
        </div>
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// rule:</span> anything that could plausibly be a Markdown file is a Markdown file. Code is for moving tokens between files and into the model.
        </div>
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// constraint:</span> outputs are shared across seats; reasoning is private. Closer to how real executives operate.
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       04. PROVENANCE
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="04-provenance">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div class="section-number">04 — PROVENANCE</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Where this comes from</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="content-row">
      <div class="content-body">
        <p>
          Three pieces of prior work made this tractable, and all three are named
          honestly. Peter Steinberger's OpenClaw supplied the personal-agent pattern —
          a folder of Markdown files and a model that reads them on startup — which
          is the primitive Tokenwright scales up one layer. The token-economy essay,
          published 2026-04-17, is the public articulation of the thesis this site
          extends. A forty-eight-hour academic-length paper, built by a purpose-built
          writing harness, is the existence proof that the pattern produces real
          outputs at pace.
        </p>
        <p>
          None of this is a surprise in hindsight. All of the components existed. The
          specific move Tokenwright makes is to stop treating the harness as a
          property of a single agent and start treating it as the property of an
          organisation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="content-margin">
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// source:</span> OpenClaw — <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw" rel="noopener">openclaw/openclaw</a>.
        </div>
        <div class="annotation">
          <span class="prefix">// source:</span> <a href="https://connoratkins.ai/blog/the-token-economy" rel="noopener">connoratkins.ai/blog/the-token-economy</a>.
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       05. STATUS
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="05-status">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div class="section-number">05 — STATUS</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Where this is, stated plainly</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="content-row">
      <div class="content-body">
        <p>
          Tokenwright is being built by a four-person founding team in Swansea,
          Wales. What exists in the open today is this specification, the
          personal site at <a href="https://connoratkins.ai" rel="noopener">connoratkins.ai</a>,
          and two design repositories under active revision. No traction is
          claimed because none is the point yet. The artefact is the
          specification. Honesty about scope is itself the institutional signal.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="content-margin">
        <div class="annotation">
